                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2314: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-19T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 19, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 19—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>256. Your 156, May 18, 8 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>At the Leticia Advisory Committee meeting this morning the President of
                        the Committee read out a communication from Mello Franco as well as
                        statements made to him by the Peruvian and Colombian delegates to the effect
                        that complete agreement had been reached at Rio covering all the points at
                        issue.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Committee is making an appropriate statement to the Council which has
                        the matter on its agenda for this afternoon.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
